00:56:30.270 --> 00:56:32.850
VIET THANH NGUYEN: --from
the comments that I hear

00:56:32.850 --> 00:56:34.710
in Vietnamese, in
Vietnamese-language

00:56:34.710 --> 00:56:36.450
communities, and so on--

00:56:36.450 --> 00:56:39.990
the casual racism, the
deeply embedded prejudices

00:56:39.990 --> 00:56:41.040
that people have.

00:56:41.040 --> 00:56:42.870
What it goes to show
is that it doesn't

00:56:42.870 --> 00:56:44.565
matter if you are a minority.

00:56:44.565 --> 00:56:46.440
Just because you've been
the victim of racism

00:56:46.440 --> 00:56:48.690
doesn't mean you can't
be a racist yourself.

00:56:48.690 --> 00:56:50.400
And as a matter of
fact, oftentimes you

00:56:50.400 --> 00:56:52.530
are a racist yourself.

00:56:52.530 --> 00:56:57.330
These are the unfortunate
dynamics of human experience.

00:56:57.330 --> 00:56:59.944
And what that meant for
me, both as a writer,

00:56:59.944 --> 00:57:02.110
but also as someone who's
Vietnamese and someone who

00:57:02.110 --> 00:57:04.440
thinks about politics
and political stories,

00:57:04.440 --> 00:57:08.290
is that my commitment
as a writer is twofold.

00:57:08.290 --> 00:57:10.920
One is that it is certainly
to the Vietnamese community,

00:57:10.920 --> 00:57:13.570
and to tell our stories
and all that kind of thing.

00:57:13.570 --> 00:57:17.250
But the second obligation
is to truth and justice,

00:57:17.250 --> 00:57:18.960
to use these grand words.

00:57:18.960 --> 00:57:23.280
And if your community is
doing something wrong,

00:57:23.280 --> 00:57:25.950
you need to stand up against it.

00:57:25.950 --> 00:57:28.230
That's the role of the writer.

00:57:28.230 --> 00:57:30.450
The role of the
writer is complex.

00:57:30.450 --> 00:57:34.590
It's both to represent,
but it's also to oppose.

00:57:34.590 --> 00:57:37.324
And again, the dynamics of being
a minority in this country,

00:57:37.324 --> 00:57:39.240
or any country, oftentimes,
is you feel simply

00:57:39.240 --> 00:57:40.430
the desire to represent.

00:57:40.430 --> 00:57:42.150
We've been misrepresented.

00:57:42.150 --> 00:57:43.810
There's not been
enough representation.

00:57:43.810 --> 00:57:46.290
Therefore, we have to represent.

00:57:46.290 --> 00:57:50.550
But again, if your community
is doing something wrong,

00:57:50.550 --> 00:57:53.400
you have to represent that.

00:57:53.400 --> 00:57:57.900
Now, that is the real
challenge, I think.

00:57:57.900 --> 00:58:01.320
And if we think of
ourselves as Americans,

00:58:01.320 --> 00:58:06.060
many American writers do
not go out there thinking

00:58:06.060 --> 00:58:07.510
we have to represent America.

00:58:07.510 --> 00:58:09.930
That's not the first thing
that most American writers

00:58:09.930 --> 00:58:11.350
or artists are thinking about.

00:58:11.350 --> 00:58:13.700
They're thinking, my first
obligation is to the art,

00:58:13.700 --> 00:58:15.760
and then it's to the
truth and justice.

00:58:15.760 --> 00:58:18.942
And it's oftentimes in
opposition to America itself.

00:58:18.942 --> 00:58:21.150
Either America, in terms of
what it's doing overseas,

00:58:21.150 --> 00:58:24.750
or America, what's happening
wrong within our country today,

00:58:24.750 --> 00:58:26.550
whatever that happens to be.

00:58:26.550 --> 00:58:29.370
That's part of what it means
to be a part of the majority.

00:58:29.370 --> 00:58:31.650
And that's also, if you're
a minority writer, that's

00:58:31.650 --> 00:58:33.210
what you have to do, as well.

00:58:33.210 --> 00:58:38.245
You cannot feel that your
first obligation is only

00:58:38.245 --> 00:58:40.620
to your ethnicity or your
culture or something like that.

00:58:40.620 --> 00:58:42.900
That's part of it, but
the first obligations

00:58:42.900 --> 00:58:45.720
are to your principles,
your art, truth, justice,

00:58:45.720 --> 00:58:46.960
things like that.

00:58:46.960 --> 00:58:50.340
And so that's part
of, I think, what's

00:58:50.340 --> 00:58:54.450
going to happen with something
like Vietnamese-American

00:58:54.450 --> 00:58:57.260
writing and so on.

00:58:57.260 --> 00:58:59.010
They have to depict
those kinds of things.

00:58:59.010 --> 00:59:01.380
They have to depict both
the beauty of Little Saigon,

00:59:01.380 --> 00:59:04.930
but also, of course, the
fact that it's a deeply--

00:59:04.930 --> 00:59:07.900
it's almost a fascistic
community out there.

00:59:07.900 --> 00:59:13.350
And you step out of line,
they will get in your face,

00:59:13.350 --> 00:59:15.990
and make sure you
don't say another word.

00:59:15.990 --> 00:59:18.510
Thank you very much, Google,
